<subSubSection id="C3086571FF9A145DFF26F86C8662FE24" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAD36FAFF9A145DFF26F86C8662FE24" blockId="12.[151,1436,1929,2033]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,152,526]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B966EAE8FF9A145CFF26F86C8220F82E" bold="true" box="[197,326,1968,1994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C124D79FF9A145CFEADF86D812AF82E" box="[334,588,1969,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metachrostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miasma">
<emphasis id="B966EAE8FF9A145CFEADF86D812AF82E" box="[334,588,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Metachrostis miasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D79FF9A145CFD08F86D803FF82E" box="[747,857,1969,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metachrostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinevi">
<emphasis id="B966EAE8FF9A145CFD08F86D803FF82E" box="[747,857,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. sinevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its darker brown coloration and wing pattern (see diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D79FF9A145CFE95F80B8281F814" box="[374,487,2007,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metachrostis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinevi">
<emphasis id="B966EAE8FF9A145CFE95F80B8281F814" box="[374,487,2007,2032]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. sinevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a narrower valva without extension on its dorsal margin, and by a relatively thinner and longer aedeagus with a thin, constricted coecum and small proximal extension. Adult (
<figureCitation id="13292A7FFF9B145DFAD7FF4486E8FF56" box="[1332,1422,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 22" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[184,1410,751,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[163,1428,724,1875]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 22. Eublemminae spp., adults. 17. Metachrostis sinevi, male, holotype, Russia, Primorye terr. (ZISP); 18. Metachrostis sinevi, male, paratype, Russia, Khabarovsk terr. (ZISP); 19. Metachrostis miasma, male (after Yoshimoto, 1999), Japan; 20. Odice arcuinna, female, Austria (ZFMK); 21. Eublemma amoena, female, Spain (Coll. G. Behounek); 22. Eublemma melabela, male, Tadjikistan (ZISP)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274742/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDA24DDFF9B145DFA8EFF4486E8FF56" box="[1389,1422,152,178]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan: 
<quantity id="4CEA9B1FFF9B145DFEFEFF6282C7FF3C" box="[285,417,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="16.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="16.0">16–17 mm</quantity>
. Head, body and wings dark greyish-brown; in wing pattern all crosslines lines black; basal and subbasal fields not darker than background; antemedial line thin; medial line widely shadowed on inner side; postmedial line distinct, thin, waved; orbicular spot dark brown; reniform spot grey-brown, with dark-brown borders. Subterminal field between postmedial and submarginal lines with dark-brown waved band. In male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13292A7FFF9B145DFE56FE85816DFE97" box="[437,523,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 32" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1501,1525]" captionTargetBox="[186,1397,352,1453]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,339,1475]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 32. Metachrostis spp., male genitalia. 29. M. batanga, paratype, prep. 2090 VK ZFMK, China (ZFMK); 30. M. hoenei, paratype, prep. 2089 VK ZFMK, China (ZFMK); 31. M. sinevi, holotype, prep. 0 0 35 Matov, Russia, Primorye terr. (ZISP); 32. M. miasma, (after Yoshimoto, 1999), Japan." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274744/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDA24DDFF9B145DFE0FFE85816DFE97" box="[492,523,345,371]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
) uncus curved; valva narrow with parallel dorsal and ventral margins; ventral margin extended medially and with slightly constrictde distally; aedeagus relatively thin and long with long, constricted coecum; proximal extension of aedeagus small, oval. Female genitalia not examined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
